  <name>Screenshot Tool</name>
  <summary>Capture and edit screenshots with annotation tools</summary>
  
  <developer id="io.github.rodsilvaviera2">
    <name>rodsilvaviera2</name>
  </developer>
  
  <description>
    <p>
      Screenshot Tool is a modern screenshot utility for GNOME that allows you to 
      capture, annotate, and share screenshots with ease.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Capture full screen, individual windows, or selected areas</li>
      <li>Built-in image editor with annotation tools</li>
      <li>Drawing tools: pen, rectangle, ellipse, arrow, and text</li>
      <li>Color picker for custom annotations</li>
      <li>Crop and resize captured images</li>
      <li>Copy to clipboard or save to file</li>
      <li>Modern GTK4/libadwaita interface following GNOME design guidelines</li>
      <li>Keyboard shortcuts for quick capture</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
  
